      "content": "Eugenicists in the early 20th century used a variety of pseudoscientific methods and biased interpretations of data to support their claims of racial hierarchies. They often cited flawed intelligence tests, such as the Stanford-Binet test, which were designed to measure \"mental deficiency\" and were biased against certain racial and ethnic groups. They also used craniometry, the measurement of skull size and shape, to argue that certain races had smaller and supposedly less capable brains. Physical measurements, such as height and body mass index, were also used to claim that some races were inherently less capable. These biased data were presented as scientific proof of racial superiority and inferiority, despite being deeply flawed and influenced by the eugenicists' own prejudices. They used these supposed \"scientific\" findings to justify discriminatory policies and practices, such as forced sterilizations and restrictive immigration laws, under the guise of improving the genetic quality of the population.",
